President Obama thanked Secretary of Transportation Ray LaHood for his dedication, hard work, and years of service to the American people. He praised LaHood's outstanding work over the last four years as Secretary of Transportation and thanked him for his friendship. The President highlighted their shared belief that public servants owe their allegiance to the people they represent rather than to a party or faction. As Secretary of Transportation, LaHood focused on creating jobs and growing the economy by rebuilding roads, bridges, and transit systems. He also made significant investments in the passenger rail system and laid the groundwork for a high-speed rail network. The President acknowledged LaHood's commitment to making the entire transportation system safer and stronger, benefiting all Americans who travel by air, rail, or highway. Finally, President Obama expressed his gratitude to LaHood and wished him the best in the future.